<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="376" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,573,1069]" pageId="6" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,934,960]" pageId="6" pageNumber="376">Remarks</emphasis>
. This seems to be the smallest species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[811,899,935,960]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vara">
<emphasis box="[811,899,935,960]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="376">M. vara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup and is easily recognized by the extensively shiny body. See for further remarks under 
<taxonomicName box="[699,826,970,996]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Myolepta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[699,826,970,996]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="376">M. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
